<h2 class="sectionedit1"><a name="exp" id="exp">exp</a></h2>
<div class="level2">

<p>
Syntaxe :
</p>
<pre class="cpp code cpp">    <span class="co2">#include &lt;cmath&gt;</span>
    <span class="kw4">double</span> <span class="kw3">exp</span> <span class="br0">&#40;</span><span class="kw4">double</span> arg<span class="br0">&#41;</span><span class="sy4">;</span></pre>
<p>
La fonction <code>exp()</code> renvoie <a href="http://fr.wikipedia.org/wiki/E_(nombre)" class="urlextern" title="http://fr.wikipedia.org/wiki/E_(nombre)"  rel="nofollow">e (2.7182818...)</a> élevé à la puissance <code>arg</code>.
</p>

<p>
Le C++ fournit également les implémentations suivantes :

</p>
<pre class="cpp code cpp">    <span class="co2">#include &lt;cmath&gt;</span>
    <span class="kw4">float</span> <span class="kw3">exp</span> <span class="br0">&#40;</span><span class="kw4">float</span> arg<span class="br0">&#41;</span><span class="sy4">;</span> <span class="co1">// identique à expf() en C99</span>
    <span class="kw4">long</span> <span class="kw4">double</span> <span class="kw3">exp</span> <span class="br0">&#40;</span><span class="kw4">long</span> <span class="kw4">double</span> arg<span class="br0">&#41;</span><span class="sy4">;</span> <span class="co1">// identique à expl() en C99</span></pre>
<p>
